class.description:
[LSystem] stores an L-system definition (axiom, rewrite rules, iteration settings) and generates segment data for 2D/3D use.

Generation supports callback symbols via [member opcode_callbacks]. When a callback symbol is encountered, [LSystem] invokes the mapped method on the context node passed to [method generate_2d] or [method generate_3d]. Callback methods receive an [code]l_system_info[/code] [Dictionary] with runtime values ([code]length[/code] and [code]angle[/code]) and the mutable payload dictionary. Updating [code]l_system_info.length[/code] or [code]l_system_info.angle[/code] changes subsequent traversal behavior.

Callback payload is a mutable [Dictionary]. The payload starts from [member data], is updated by callbacks, and is copied into each future generated segment as [code]extra_data[/code]. Branching ([code][[/code] and [code]][/code]) preserves/restores payload state, [code]l_system_info[/code] values, and turtle position/direction.

Example usage:
[codeblock lang=gdscript]
@export var l_system: LSystem

func _ready() -> void:
	l_system.data = {"thickness": 8.0}
	l_system.opcode_callbacks = {"T": "taper"}
	var result = l_system.generate_2d(self)

func taper(l_system_info: Dictionary, extra_data: Dictionary) -> void:
	extra_data["thickness"] = max(0.5, float(extra_data.get("thickness", 8.0)) * 0.9)
[/codeblock]

In this example, each [code]T[/code] callback symbol updates [code]thickness[/code] for future generated segments.
